import React from 'react' import { useState } from 'react' import Calculator from './calculator' import './App.css' const App = () => { const [calc, setCalc] = useState('0') const [firstOperand, setFirstOperand] = useState(null) const [operator, setOperator] = useState(null) const [secondOperand, setSecondOperand] = useState(null) const operators = ['+', '-', 'x', '÷'] function reset() { setFirstOperand(null) setOperator(null) setSecondOperand(null) } const updateDisplay = (value) => { if (value === 'C/CE') { setCalc('0') reset() return } if (value === 'OFF') { setCalc('') reset() return } setCalc(value) if(secondOperand === null) { setFirstOperand(value) console.log(firstOperand) } } return (
) } export default App
